title: Cajun Cabbage with Rice
summary: You can never have too many Creole recipes, so give Cajun Cabbage with Rice a try. This recipe makes 6 servings with 431 calories, 23g of protein, and 25g of fat each. For $1.57 per serving, this recipe covers 27% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. 1 person has made this recipe and would make it again. It works best as a main course, and is done in approximately 1 hour and 35 minutes. If you have vegetable oil, bell pepper, ground pepper, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. To use up the salt you could follow this main course with the Apple Turnovers Recipe as a dessert. It is brought to you by Allrecipes. It is a good option if you're following a gluten free diet. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 61%. This score is solid. Similar recipes are Cajun Cabbage, Cajun Cabbage, and Cajun Cabbage.

winePairing.pairingText: Cajun works really well with Albarino, Sauvignon Blanc, and rosé Wine. These low-tannin, lower alcohol wines will complement the heat in spicy cajun dishes, instead of making your mouth burn more. The Eighty Four Albarino with a 4.1 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 28 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: Eighty Four Albarino
productMatches.description: This is springtime in a bottle. The aromas and flavors are silky, sunny citrus blossom, white peach, honeysuckle, and dried apricot with a touch of lavender. Thanks to the lively acidity and austere minerality this abundance of fruit is clean and energetic from start to finish.

instructions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).                            Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Brown together the beef, green pepper, onion, and garlic until the meat is no longer pink and the vegetables have softened, about 8 minutes. Drain liquid from pan.                            Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, rice, salt, basil, oregano, and the cayenne, white, and black pepper (adding more pepper to taste, if desired). Spread mixture into an ungreased 9x12-inch baking pan. Top with cabbage and Colby cheese.                            Cover and bake in preheated oven for 65 to 75 minutes, or until the rice is tender. steps.step: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).
Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Brown together the beef, green pepper, onion, and garlic until the meat is no longer pink and the vegetables have softened, about 8 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, rice, salt, basil, oregano, and the cayenne, white, and black pepper (adding more pepper to taste, if desired).
Spread mixture into an ungreased 9x12-inch baking pan. Top with cabbage and Colby cheese.
Cover and bake in preheated oven for 65 to 75 minutes, or until the rice is tender.
